home_frameset manufacturing strategy ms&e 268 to be offered in spring 2003 by prof robert c carlson home contact course description what is ms&e 268 this is a course about the development and implementation of the manufacturing functional strategy emphasis is on the integration of manufacturing strategy with the business and the corporate strategies a manufacturing based firm topics types of manufacturing technologies and their characteristics quality management capacity planning and facilities choice the organization and control of operations determination of manufacturing's role in corporate strategy prerequisites graduate student 260 or 261 the course is 3 units ms&e 268 is offered by management science & engineering ms&e department at stanford university
